entry.title: Allow same-site prefetches to be made in the default network context.
entry.content:
Previously only same-origin URLs could be prefetched in the default

network context. This CL changes it so same-site prefetches are made in

the default network context, and cross-site prefetches are made in

isolated network contexts.



The narrow case of same-site cross-origin prefetches that require the

prefetch proxy are blocked, because it would require configuring the

default network context to use the proxy for just those prefetches. This

is tracked in a separate bug crbug.com/1439986.

entry.title: Use a variant to hold the data to write to the clipboard.
entry.content:
Previously, this was just an enum + a vector of vector of bytes. This

ends up being fairly unwieldy *and* not typesafe: for example, the

bitmap type was smuggling the data through by serializing a pointer's

representation as bytes into the vector, extracting it on the other

side, and stuffing the bytes back into a pointer-shaped value.



This also allows for the various Write*() functions to take more

well-typed arguments instead of pointer + size pairs, eliminating some

wasteful conversions between byte vectors and strings.

entry.title: [scheduler] Fix how page freeze and audio state tracking interact
entry.content:
PageSchedulerImpl's PageLifecycleState can get out of sync with the

frozen state if a recently audible state is frozen, for example if a

a recently audible page is put in BFCache. OnAudioSilent() sets the

PageLifecycleState to kHiddenBackgrounded even if the page was frozen,

which is not the correct state. This is causing the frozen page count

in the MemoryPurgeManager to be incorrect, which is triggering DCHECKs.



This CL fixes the state tracking so that

1. OnAudioSilent() handles frozen pages (they should still transition

to silent, but shouldn't change the PageLifecycleState).

2. Recently audible pages transition to silent immediately upon

freezing.

3. AudioStateChange handles frozen pages, transitioning them to

silent. This handles the case where the page is frozen before the

audio state change notification is sent.

entry.title: lacros/color: preload common colorspaces
entry.content:
The Chrome Color Management protocol currently needs a roundtrip between

the client and server the first time a colorspace is requested for use.

This means for certain content the first frame will be in a wrong or

default colorspace before switching over to the correct one. This can

cause flashing.



This CL mitigates the issue some by preloading the colorspaces commonly

seen on the web (youtube, google meets, hdr content) so they are ready

the first time they are requested.

entry.title: Do not crash if image first visibility detected twice
entry.content:
Lazy load image visibility information is tracked with an intersection

observer on the local root (visibility_metrics_observer_), and the data

is stored on the Element itself (see: visible_load_time_metrics_ on

HTMLImageElement). This visibility information is only used for metrics.

This patch fixes a crash when the visibility information was set twice

due to two visibility metrics intersection observers.



How can there be two visibility metrics intersection observers? An

element's local root can change if the element moves between frames,

such as if an element is moved from a2 to a1 in the following tree:

Frame a1 (local root)

Frame b (remote)

Frame a2 (local root)

An element can be moved between a1 and a2, causing one visibility

metrics intersection observer for each local root.



A regression test was used to write this patch (crrev.com/c/4498925)

but the test is complex and brittle. The maintenance cost of this test

is not worth the coverage for this rare metrics DCHECK.

entry.content:
WPT must be designed to run on a wide variety of hardware and refresh

rates. Many of the tests have been retrofitted to accommodate test

hardware with very slow refresh rates, but some tests (like this one)

can fail when run on hardware with very *fast* refresh rates, because

500 animation frames may not be enough to reach the end of a scroll

animation.



With this change, we wait for 200 milliseconds and a minimum of 5

animation frames where the scroll offset doesn't change, with a

timeout after 8 seconds.

entry.title: [iOS] Fix compromised state of password is not updated after an edit
entry.content:
This CL rolls back a change made in the PasswordDetailsMediator (see

link below) to again use the list of insecure credentials provided by

the IOSChromePasswordCheckManager to determine whether a credential is

compromised or not. The list of insecure credentials was indeed

necessary because the `_credentials` list contained in the

PasswordDetailsMediator is not updated when a credential is edited in

the details page. Because of that, the updates on a credential were not

always correctly reflected in the details page. This change also removes

entry.title: Swap frame site for top-level frame site in nonced cookie partitions
entry.content:
This is to align CookiePartitionKey's implementation of nonced

partitions with StorageKey, which uses the storage origin for the

top-level site. This mismatch prevents nonced partitioned workers from

accessing partitioned cookies in the frame that registered them's

partition, since partitioned workers derive their CookiePartitionKey

from their StorageKey.



Even with this change, the nonced partitions are still unique and ephemeral.



The WPT I added checks that workers registered by credentialless frames can access partitioned cookies set by the frame that registered them.

Before this change, this test would fail.

entry.title: Ensure on-page javascript runs for single-page apps
entry.content:
This patch ensures that the on-page meta extraction for product info

in the shopping service runs for different navigations in single-page

web apps. The 'DidFinishedLoading' signal is still used, but is

supplemented by 'DidStopLoading' which is observed after a navigation

has finished. The script is run 2 seconds after the last "stopped

loading" event and is still only run once per unique page. Coverage

will be higher as a result of this work.



The added delay in running javascript also impacts how a number of

metrics are recorded in the shopping service. Specifically, if a

user navigates prior to getting a result from the javascript, the

metric will not be recorded. This impacts the following:



- Commerce.ShoppingService.ProductInfo.FallbackDataContent

- Commerce.ShoppingService.ProductInfo.FallbackDataUsed

- Commerce.ShoppingService.ProductInfo.ImageAvailability

entry.title: [SuperSize] Add ARSC Count Metrics.
entry.content:
This CL adds ARSC metrics data (counts of types for each ARSC file) to

.size files, updates the Viewer to show them, and changes Metrics Tree

subcategories from "SIZE metrics" / "COUNT metrics" to "Size" / "Count".



In the Metrics View, items were previously classified as "ELF" or "DEX"

by checking whether or not the metric suffix (e.g., "SIZE/.text" =>

".text") has "." (e.g., ".text" has "." => "ELF"). However, we're now

adding "ARSC" to the mix, making the old scheme is obsolete.



The new classification scheme is to examine, for each metric item, the

extensions of associated files (files shown as table rows). For Chrome,

we consistently have ".so" => "ELF", ".dex"=> "DEX", ".arsc" => "ARSC",

allowing easy classification. To handle edge cases, we also assign empty

extension => "ELF" and mixed / unknown extension => "OTHER".



Details:

* apk.py: CreateArscSymbols(): For each RES_TABLE_TYPE_TYPE chunk,

create count metrics entry, e.g., "COUNT/anim" -> 100.

* archive.py: _CreateContainerSymbols(): Add the above.

* ui-base.js: Add helper getFileExtension().

* state.js: Add metrics icon "arsc" and "other", reusing existing ones.

* metrics-tree-ui.js: MetricsTreeModel:

* makeMetricNode(): Implement the new metric item classification

scheme via file extensions.

* extractAndStoreRoot(): Change subcategory names; create Sets of

associated extensions for each metric item for classification.

entry.title: Enforce the disabling of unpublished extensions by enterprise policy
entry.content:
Integrate the work done in past CLs, i.e., policy definition, policy

check function and retrieving publish status using CWSInfoService.

Specifically:

- Create a new disable reason, PUBLISHED_IN_STORE_REQUIRED_BY_POLICY.

- Modify StandardManagementPolicy provider's MustRemainDisabled method

to use the check function and return the new disable reason.

- Modify ExtensionService::CheckManagementPolicy to disable/enable

extensions as a result of this check.

- Make ExtensionService observe CWSInfoService for metadata (publish

status) changes and also request metadata fetch when necessary.



Bug: 1406308
